  "text": "In our previous miRNA microarray, the expression level of miR-224 in cervical cancer tissues was raised to 2.32-fold compared with that in normal cervical tissues [CITATION_1] . In our present study, the expression level of miR-224 was raised by 1.82-fold (P = 0.0025) in cervical cancer tissues compared with that in normal tissues (Fig 1A) . Correlation between miR-224 expression level and clinicopathological characters of cervical cancer was summarized in Table 2 . The miR-224 high-expressers were significantly associated with advanced FIGO stage, nodal metastasis, larger tumor size, vascular involvement and deep stromal invasion (all P<0.05), suggesting that higher expression level of miR-224 may be involved in the progression and metastasis of cervical cancer.",
